<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!--
  Robotiq 2F-140 parallel gripper macro (vendored).

  Source: PickNikRobotics/ros2_robotiq_gripper, robotiq_description package
    https://github.com/PickNikRobotics/ros2_robotiq_gripper
    robotiq_description/urdf/robotiq_2f_140_macro.urdf.xacro
    robotiq_description/urdf/robotiq_2f_140.xacro

  Adapted for the genie_sim_robot_model layout, mirroring the sister
  robotiq_2f_85 macro one-for-one:

    - The two upstream files (robotiq_2f_140_macro.urdf.xacro entry-point
      and robotiq_2f_140.xacro finger-side helpers) are inlined into this
      single self-contained xacro, matching the flat layout of
      robotiq_2f_85_macro.urdf.xacro.
    - Mesh URIs rewritten from package://robotiq_description/meshes/{visual,collision}/2f_140/...
      to package://genie_sim_robot_model/robots/universal_robots/ur5/gripper/robotiq_140/meshes/{visual,collision}/...
      (all 6 STLs: base_link, coupling, outer_knuckle, outer_finger,
      inner_knuckle, inner_finger; collision shares the visual STL set).
    - The ros2_control include and the 2f_140.ros2_control.xacro
      transmission helper are dropped: this macro is description-only.
      Grippers are simulated through Isaac Sim joint commands rather than
      ros2_control, mirroring how arx_x5 / agilex_piper / 2F-85 grippers
      are wired in this workspace.
    - Link / joint names use the active/passive convention introduced by
      the 2F-85 macro:
        * 'active' replaces upstream 'left'  (the side carrying the master DOF).
        * 'passive' replaces upstream 'right' (the mimic-driven side).
      The literal words 'left' / 'right' are dropped to avoid an arbitrary
      handedness convention. Names emitted by this macro:
        Active-side links:  gripper_active_outer_link, gripper_active_inner_link,
                            gripper_active_outer_finger_link, gripper_active_finger_tip_link,
                            gripper_active_finger_pad_link
        Passive-side links: gripper_passive_outer_link, gripper_passive_inner_link,
                            gripper_passive_outer_finger_link, gripper_passive_finger_tip_link,
                            gripper_passive_finger_pad_link
        Master DOF:         gripper_active_master_joint (drives gripper_active_outer_link;
                            this is upstream 'finger_joint', the canonical Robotiq
                            drive; suffix '_master' is a role-based rename adopted
                            to sidestep the importer bug described below.)
        Active-side mimics: gripper_active_slave_joint  (drives gripper_active_inner_link),
                            gripper_active_tip_joint    (= upstream left_inner_finger_joint)
        Passive-side mimics:gripper_passive_master_joint (drives gripper_passive_outer_link),
                            gripper_passive_slave_joint  (drives gripper_passive_inner_link),
                            gripper_passive_tip_joint   (= upstream right_inner_finger_joint)
        Fixed connectors:   gripper_active_outer_finger_fixed, gripper_passive_outer_finger_fixed
                            (= upstream {side}_outer_finger_joint),
                            gripper_active_pad_fixed, gripper_passive_pad_fixed
                            (= upstream {side}_inner_finger_pad_joint)
    - Kinematics, inertials, joint limits, and mimic relationships are
      preserved verbatim (single master DOF; five revolute mimics with
      multipliers +1/-1 matching upstream; two outer-finger fixed
      connectors; two finger-pad fixed connectors).
    - The upstream 'robotiq_base_link' / 'robotiq_base_joint' shim — which
      applied an Rz(pi/2) to align the 2F-140 with the 2F-85 mount frame —
      is dropped: the arm macro already provides 'gripper_base_link' as
      the canonical mount point, and the Rz(pi/2) is baked into the
      'gripper_base_inertia_fixed' joint origin so that the 2F-140 lines
      up identically to the 2F-85 on the same parent. Likewise the
      upstream 'robotiq_140_base_link' redirection layer is dropped: the
      gripper attaches its visual/collision/inertial content directly onto
      ${parent}_inertia (matches the 2F-85 macro).
    - The procedural inner_finger_pad (a small box-mesh pad with rubber
      friction) is preserved as gripper_{active,passive}_finger_pad_link
      attached via a fixed joint to the finger-tip link. It is auxiliary
      cosmetic + contact geometry; only the 5 revolute mimic joints + 1
      master joint are listed in robot.yml's joint_groups.gripper (same
      shape as the 2F-85 entry).

  Upstream license: BSD-3-Clause
-->
<robot xmlns:xacro="http://wiki.ros.org/xacro" name="robotiq_gripper">
    <xacro:macro name="robotiq_2f_140_gripper" params="
        prefix
        parent">

        <xacro:property name="mesh_dir"
            value="package://genie_sim_robot_model/robots/universal_robots/ur5/gripper/robotiq_140/meshes" />

        <!-- Gripper body: visual / collision / inertial of the upstream
             'robotiq_140_base_link' are attached directly to the parent
             (gripper_base_link from the arm macro) so we do not introduce
             a redundant link + identity-fixed joint. The Rz(pi/2) that
             upstream applied via its 'robotiq_base_link' shim is baked
             into this fixed joint's rpy so the 2F-140 mounts at the same
             orientation as the 2F-85. -->
        <link name="${parent}_inertia">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="8.625E-08 -4.6583E-06 0.03145" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.22652" />
                <inertia ixx="0.00020005" ixy="-4.2442E-10" ixz="-2.9069E-10" iyy="0.00017832" iyz="-3.4402E-08" izz="0.00013478" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_base_link.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_base_link.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_base_inertia_fixed" type="fixed">
            <parent link="${parent}" />
            <child link="${parent}_inertia" />
            <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 ${pi/2}" />
        </joint>

        <!-- ===== Active-side (upstream 'left') links ===== -->
        <link name="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="-0.000200000000003065 0.0199435877845359 0.0292245259211331" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.00853198276973456" />
                <inertia ixx="2.89328108496468E-06" ixy="-1.57935047237397E-19" ixz="-1.93980378593255E-19" iyy="1.86719750325683E-06" iyz="-1.21858577871576E-06" izz="1.21905238907251E-06" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_outer_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.792156862745098 0.819607843137255 0.933333333333333 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_outer_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_finger_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.00030115855001899 0.0373907951953854 -0.0208027427000385" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.022614240507152" />
                <inertia ixx="1.52518312458174E-05" ixy="9.76583423954399E-10" ixz="-5.43838577022588E-10" iyy="6.17694243867776E-06" iyz="6.78636130740228E-06" izz="1.16494917907219E-05" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_outer_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_outer_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_active_inner_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.000123011831763771 0.0507850843201817 0.00103968640075166" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.0271177346495152" />
                <inertia ixx="2.61910379223783E-05" ixy="-2.43616858946494E-07" ixz="-6.37789906117123E-09" iyy="2.8270243746167E-06" iyz="-5.37200748039765E-07" izz="2.83695868220296E-05" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_inner_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_inner_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_active_finger_tip_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.000299999999999317 0.0160078233491243 -0.0136945669206257" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.0104003125914103" />
                <inertia ixx="2.71909453810972E-06" ixy="1.35402465472579E-21" ixz="-7.1817349065269E-22" iyy="7.69100314106116E-07" iyz="6.74715432769696E-07" izz="2.30315190420171E-06" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_inner_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_inner_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_active_finger_pad_link">
    <inertial>
      <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0"/>
      <mass value="0.001"/>
      <inertia ixx="1e-6" iyy="1e-6" izz="1e-6" ixy="0" ixz="0" iyz="0"/>
    </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <box size="0.027 0.065 0.0075" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.9 0.9 0.9 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <box size="0.03 0.07 0.0075" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.9 0.0 0.0 1" />
                </material>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <!-- ===== Passive-side (upstream 'right') links ===== -->
        <link name="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="-0.000200000000003065 0.0199435877845359 0.0292245259211331" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.00853198276973456" />
                <inertia ixx="2.89328108496468E-06" ixy="-1.57935047237397E-19" ixz="-1.93980378593255E-19" iyy="1.86719750325683E-06" iyz="-1.21858577871576E-06" izz="1.21905238907251E-06" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_outer_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.792156862745098 0.819607843137255 0.933333333333333 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_outer_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_finger_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.00030115855001899 0.0373907951953854 -0.0208027427000385" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.022614240507152" />
                <inertia ixx="1.52518312458174E-05" ixy="9.76583423954399E-10" ixz="-5.43838577022588E-10" iyy="6.17694243867776E-06" iyz="6.78636130740228E-06" izz="1.16494917907219E-05" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_outer_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_outer_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_passive_inner_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.000123011831763771 0.0507850843201817 0.00103968640075166" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.0271177346495152" />
                <inertia ixx="2.61910379223783E-05" ixy="-2.43616858946494E-07" ixz="-6.37789906117123E-09" iyy="2.8270243746167E-06" iyz="-5.37200748039765E-07" izz="2.83695868220296E-05" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_inner_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_inner_knuckle.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_passive_finger_tip_link">
            <inertial>
                <origin xyz="0.000299999999999317 0.0160078233491243 -0.0136945669206257" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <mass value="0.0104003125914103" />
                <inertia ixx="2.71909453810972E-06" ixy="1.35402465472579E-21" ixz="-7.1817349065269E-22" iyy="7.69100314106116E-07" iyz="6.74715432769696E-07" izz="2.30315190420171E-06" />
            </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/visual/robotiq_2f_140_inner_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.1 0.1 0.1 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <mesh filename="${mesh_dir}/collision/robotiq_2f_140_inner_finger.stl" />
                </geometry>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <link name="${prefix}gripper_passive_finger_pad_link">
    <inertial>
      <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0"/>
      <mass value="0.001"/>
      <inertia ixx="1e-6" iyy="1e-6" izz="1e-6" ixy="0" ixz="0" iyz="0"/>
    </inertial>
            <visual>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <box size="0.027 0.065 0.0075" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.9 0.9 0.9 1" />
                </material>
            </visual>
            <collision>
                <origin xyz="0 0 0" rpy="0 0 0" />
                <geometry>
                    <box size="0.03 0.07 0.0075" />
                </geometry>
                <material name="">
                    <color rgba="0.9 0.0 0.0 1" />
                </material>
            </collision>
        </link>

        <!-- ===== Joints ===== -->
        <!-- Master DOF: drives the active-side outer knuckle.
             Upstream 'finger_joint'. Kinematically the canonical Robotiq
             drive (driving the inner knuckle as master instead causes
             dynamics instability). Renamed to '_master' so it sorts before
             its '_slave' siblings under parent ${parent} and is therefore
             authored on the USD stage before any mimic follower processes
             it (Isaac Sim importer alphabetical-order bug; see 2F-85 macro
             header for the full explanation). -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${parent}" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 -0.030601 0.054905" rpy="${pi / 2 + .725} 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <!-- Limits match the 2F-85 macro's working values
                 (effort="50" velocity="0.5"). The Isaac Sim URDF→USD
                 importer authors a too-soft DriveAPI (stiffness=625,
                 damping=0) that cannot resist gravity-induced moment on
                 the linkage, so the gripper droops in a pose-dependent
                 way. The fix lives in genie_sim_engine's _configure_drives
                 gripper branch, which overrides only the master joint's
                 DriveAPI (stiffness=1e4, damping=10, armature=0.001) and
                 zeros out PhysxMimicJointAPI compliance on the followers.
                 No <dynamics> tag here on purpose: any non-zero damping
                 would propagate to the mimic followers' compliance and
                 fight the master's drive. -->
            <limit lower="0" upper="0.7" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Active-side inner knuckle (mimic of master).
             Upstream 'left_inner_knuckle_joint'; original multiplier vs
             upstream master was -1 (achieved upstream via axis-flip
             cancelling sign-flip). Renamed to '_slave' for alphabetical
             ordering.
             Importer caveats (see file header — same as 2F-85):
               * <mimic offset="0"> is silently routed through a code path
                 that drops physics:lower/upperLimit, producing +/-inf and
                 tripping PhysX's mimic-joint validator. So 'offset' must
                 be omitted (its URDF default is 0 anyway).
               * Axis-flip + negative multiplier is also broken in the
                 importer (same +/-inf symptom). The robust formulation
                 is: match the axis to the master ('-1 0 0') and choose
                 the multiplier sign to preserve kinematics.
             Active-side mirror: axis matches master, multiplier flips to
             +1 to net the same upstream -1 sign convention. -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_active_slave_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${parent}" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_active_inner_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 -0.0127 0.06142" rpy="${pi / 2 + .725} 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <limit lower="-0.8757" upper="0.8757" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
            <mimic joint="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" multiplier="1" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Passive-side outer knuckle (mimic of master).
             Upstream 'right_outer_knuckle_joint'; original multiplier vs
             upstream master was -1.
             Renamed to '_master' (passive role-mirror of the active master).
             Master-matched axis + multiplier=+1 matches the upstream -1
             sign convention (the extra pi Z-rotation in rpy already
             mirrors the geometry to the passive side; the axis no longer
             needs to flip). -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_passive_master_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${parent}" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.030601 0.054905" rpy="${pi / 2 + .725} 0 ${pi}" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <limit lower="-0.725" upper="0.725" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
            <mimic joint="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" multiplier="1" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Outer-finger fixed connectors (one per side).
             Upstream '{side}_outer_finger_joint'. -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_finger_fixed" type="fixed">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_finger_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.01821998610742 0.0260018192872234" rpy="0 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="1 0 0" />
        </joint>

        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_finger_fixed" type="fixed">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_finger_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.01821998610742 0.0260018192872234" rpy="0 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="1 0 0" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Passive-side inner knuckle (mimic of master).
             Upstream 'right_inner_knuckle_joint'; original multiplier vs
             upstream master was -1.
             Renamed to '_slave' for alphabetical ordering.
             Master-matched axis + multiplier=+1 (see active_slave comment
             for importer caveats). The pi Z-rotation already mirrors the
             passive side; multiplier=+1 nets the upstream -1 convention. -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_passive_slave_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${parent}" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_passive_inner_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.0127 0.06142" rpy="${pi / 2 + .725} 0 ${pi}" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <limit lower="-0.8757" upper="0.8757" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
            <mimic joint="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" multiplier="1" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Finger-tip (= upstream inner_finger) mimics (one per side).
             Upstream '{side}_inner_finger_joint'; original multiplier vs
             upstream master was +1.
             Master-matched axis: tips have an rpy of '-0.725 0 0' relative
             to their outer_finger parent (no pi Z-rotation), so the local
             axis frame matches the master frame directly. Multiplier flips
             to -1 to net the upstream +1 sign convention given the axis
             match. (See active_slave comment for importer caveats.) -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_active_tip_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_active_outer_finger_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_active_finger_tip_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.0817554015893473 -0.0282203446692936" rpy="-0.725 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <limit lower="-0.8757" upper="0.8757" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
            <mimic joint="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" multiplier="-1" />
        </joint>

        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_passive_tip_joint" type="revolute">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_passive_outer_finger_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_passive_finger_tip_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.0817554015893473 -0.0282203446692936" rpy="-0.725 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="-1 0 0" />
            <limit lower="-0.8757" upper="0.8757" velocity="0.5" effort="50" />
            <mimic joint="${prefix}gripper_active_master_joint" multiplier="-1" />
        </joint>

        <!-- Finger-pad fixed connectors (cosmetic + contact pad).
             Upstream '{side}_inner_finger_pad_joint'. -->
        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_active_pad_fixed" type="fixed">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_active_finger_tip_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_active_finger_pad_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.0457554015893473 -0.0272203446692936" rpy="0 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="0 0 1" />
        </joint>

        <joint name="${prefix}gripper_passive_pad_fixed" type="fixed">
            <parent link="${prefix}gripper_passive_finger_tip_link" />
            <child link="${prefix}gripper_passive_finger_pad_link" />
            <origin xyz="0 0.0457554015893473 -0.0272203446692936" rpy="0 0 0" />
            <axis xyz="0 0 1" />
        </joint>
    </xacro:macro>
</robot>
